org.apache.flex.compiler.common

Interface IDecoration

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IAccessibilityTagNode, IDefaultPropertyTagNode, IEffectTagNode, IEventTagNode, IEventTriggerTagNode, IInspectableTagNode, IMetaTagNode, IMultiValueMetaTagNode, INamespaceDecorationNode, IResourceBundleTagNode, IStyleTagNode, ITypedTagNode
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AccessibilityTagNode, AlternativeTagNode, BaseDefinitionMetaTagNode, BasicMetaTagNode, DefaultPropertyTagNode, EffectTagNode, EventTagNode, EventTriggerTagNode, InspectableTagNode, MetaTagNode, MultiValueMetaTagNode, NamespaceIdentifierNode, QualifiedNamespaceExpressionNode, ResourceBundleTagNode, SkinClassTagNode, StyleTagNode, TypedTagNode

    public interface IDecoration
    A IDecoration is a type of parse tree element that decorates an IDefinitionNode. An IDecoration is not a child of an IDefinitionNode node, rather it helps change the signature of the IDefinitionNode These include: -modifiers -namespaces -metadata
